The paper focuses on developing a scheme for secure and trustworthy D2D connections in Mobile Crowdsourcing Systems (MCSs). This involves addressing issues related to privacy, opportunistic encountering behaviors, and reliable peer device selections. These topics are closely related to the sub-categories of computer security (cs.CR), mobile agents (cs.MA), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), social and information networks (cs.SI), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
